##############################################################
#
#  Setup
#
#
Context("Numeric");
Context()->flags->set(tolerance=>.05);

#image scale
$imgScale = 1;

#image aspect ratio
$width = $imgScale*458;
$height = $imgScale*225;

$w =random(1,8,1);
$r =random(0.1,1,0.1);
$m =random(1,8,1);
$v =random(1,10,1);


$Ans=($w**2)*$r-0.05*(2*$w*$v+10)+$m*0;

##############################################################
#
#  PGML area
#
#
BEGIN_PGML

A steel bar is pinned at [`A`] and rotating at constant angular velocity [::omega_{A}::] [`= [$w]`] [`rad/s`] in the vertical plane. A brass collar of mass [`m= [$m]`] [`kg`] is located [`[$r]`] [`m`] away from the pin and is moving along the bar with relative velocity [::v_{B"/"A}::][` = [$v]`] [`m/s`] to the right. The coefficient of friction between the bar and the mass is [`0.05`]. Find the relative acceleration, [::(a_{B"/"A})_{xyz}::] of the collar with respect to the bar (in [`m/`][::s^2::]). Use [`g = 10`] [`m/`][::s^2::].

Hint: Write both the dynamic equations of motion and kinematic equations to solve this problem. 



[@ image( "UBC-DYN-17-054.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]* 

 [::(a_{B"/"A})_{xyz}::] = [____]{$Ans} [`m/s^2`]

END_PGML

